\section{Configuration}

The configuration keys live here because both the LaTeX integration and the CLI
need the same defaults, and they must agree even when the package is imported
outside the [[mentipy]] command.  We therefore compute the config file path from
the fixed application name, not from [[sys.argv[0]]].  The built-in settings
table also serves as the source for configuration discovery, so keys that
default to [[None]] still belong there.  In particular,
[[mentipy.base_url]] uses [[None]] to mean \enquote{resolve the LAN URL later}.

