The pop-then-reinsert protocol shows up most clearly when the lecturer
re-registers a middle question during a fresh build: it should land at the end
of the iteration order, not stay in place.  Without this rule, inserting a new
slide between two existing questions and rebuilding would leave the
\enquote{Next $\rightarrow$} link skipping over the new slide on the next
results page.

<<test functions>>=

def test_register_reinserts_questions_in_document_order(tmp_path):
    store = Store(tmp_path / "mentipy.json", min_prefix=4)
    first = OpenQuestion("Warm-up?")
    middle = OpenQuestion("Main point?")
    last = OpenQuestion("Wrap-up?")

    store.register(first)
    store.register(middle)
    store.register(last)
    store.register(middle)

    hashes = [entry["hash"] for entry in store.all_questions()]

    assert hashes == [
        question_hash(first),
