\subsection{Remembered QR artifacts}

QR regeneration needs one extra piece of operational metadata that should not
change the question's identity: the concrete files earlier renders wrote.  The
same question can appear in more than one document directory or image format,
so we remember a de-duplicated list of those QR targets beside the canonical
question payload.  We store the resolved absolute paths, because later
[[mentipy serve]] runs may happen from a different working directory than the
original render and still need to refresh the same files.

<<store methods>>=
def remember_qr_target(self, full_hash: str, qr_path: str | Path):
    """Remember that ``full_hash`` wrote a QR artifact to ``qr_path``."""

    with self._lock:
        data = self._data()

        if full_hash not in data["questions"]:
            raise KeyError(full_hash)

        meta = data["questions"][full_hash]
        target = Path(qr_path).resolve().as_posix()
        targets = meta.setdefault(QR_TARGETS_KEY, [])
        if target in targets:
            return

        targets.append(target)
        self._write(data)
@

The regeneration path returns [[Path]] objects rather than raw JSON strings so
callers can work at the filesystem abstraction level immediately.

<<store methods>>=
def qr_targets(self, full_hash: str) -> list[Path]:
    """Return remembered QR artifact paths for ``full_hash``."""

    meta = self._data()["questions"][full_hash]
    return [Path(path) for path in meta.get(QR_TARGETS_KEY, [])]
@

Rendering the same question again into the same file should not multiply the
remembered targets, and the public metadata helpers should still hide those
local paths.

<<test functions>>=
